main event: An observer discovered material on his farm that was thought to be from an aircraft, which was later identified as radar chaff.
interesting points: The incident occurred in the early hours of April 1, 1966, in Salem, Arkansas., The observer was concerned about aircraft flying over his farm without lights., The material was evaluated and concluded to be radar chaff from an aircraft on a special mission., A letter was sent to Mrs. Hunt explaining that the photos she claimed to have taken were not received by the Air Force., The report references various sighting details but does not contain any clear descriptions of photographs or images.
sighted object: material believed to be from an aircraft
